99>(11/22/02 11:04:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4574.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i know i know</span><hr size=1> Well considering i know how you feel cuz i went through this cept i went through it and had to come up with a portfolio in less than 10 minutes i think i did pretty good any ways...what you wanna do is first seperate all your works into their different stylez, then into colorized, sketches, b&amp;W and take your best of each of the three...<br>
<br>
Make sure you select peices that A) have a good color scheme B) Have good hands [a lot of places see if you can draw hands because it is considered one of the most complex thing to draw and if you can draw hands god you can draw anything] C) Have good working concepts and D) Show different aspect of a character's emotion or different ways that a character can interact with something [i.e. have a character fighting while having that character or something close to the same one in a romantic scene or a sad scene]<br>
<br>
I would also suggest as i was suggested throw in some animal drawings, realistic drawings, comic book drawings, and weapon drawings. Even if you don't draw these on a common basis you want to show case wat you can do,not what you do do.<br>
<br>
Also another thing you might consider is come up with a few story boards, scripts, background info on a character. This shows that not only can you draw but you can also put a story to what you create which a lot of artists don't do. I would also make a suggestion as to read a book and draw out the characters from that book.<br>
<br>
ok i'm done lol <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kennygeeze>Kenny Geeze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/23/02 11:09:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4574.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lespaul.com/menu1/deluxe.jpg width=080 height=110></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i know i know</span><hr size=1> Mount any flimsy paper on matte/illustration board.<br>
Design wise, sometimes it looks good to have most pieces relatively the same size, either through the drawing itself and whatever it's mounted on.<br>
Can't emphasize this enough, but lots and lots of drawings from life. Both rough gesture drawings/ sketches, value renders, and detailed studies. -- This will include people, animals, toothbrushes, rocks, cars, and everything in between. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Good luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jacksusername>Jacks username</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/23/02 1:20:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4574.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i know i know</span><hr size=1> It also depends on what kind of interviews  you are going for.  If it is a concentrated area, make sure you have plenty of that, but back it up with other mediums to make sure the employer knows what you're capapble of.  <br>
Excellent still-lifes will show you can do great observation pieces, and  mixing it with some moody artwork will also show you can present moods and depth in your artwork.  Most important is to make sure you are varied and let them know that you are up to any task they might give you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=randomtask@polykarbonbbs>Random Task</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/23/02 1:29:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4574.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i know i know</span><hr size=1> the courses that i have/will apply for are bachelor of design: visual communication and another bachelor in multimedia design... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sistaninja>sistaninja</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://emeraldwinter.com/icon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/24/02 6:52:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4574.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://emeraldwinter.com/lunava01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i know i know</span><hr size=1> How many peices should you have in a portfolio to take to a college interview and about how large should they be?  Too bad most of my best work is really small ^^;; <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.emeraldwinter.com"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://emeraldwinter.com/pkbanr.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!